friendly_name.description: The string that you assigned to describe the resource.

limits.description: An object that describes the limits of the service instance. The `limits` object contains  `channel_members` to describe the members/channel limit and `user_channels` to describe the channels/user limit. `channel_members` can be 1,000 or less, with a default of 250. `user_channels` can be 1,000 or less, with a default value of 100.

links.description: The absolute URLs of the Service's [Channels](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/channels), [Roles](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/rest/role-resource), [Bindings](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/rest/binding-resource), and [Users](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/rest/user-resource).

media.description: An object that describes the properties of media that the service supports. The object contains the `size_limit_mb` property, which describes the size of the largest media file in MB; and the `compatibility_message` property, which contains the message text to send when a media message does not have any text.

notifications.description: The notification configuration for the Service instance. See [Push Notification Configuration](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/push-notification-configuration) for more info.

post_webhook_retry_count.description: The number of times to retry a call to the `post_webhook_url` if the request times out (after 5 seconds) or it receives a 429, 503, or 504 HTTP response. The default is 0, which means the call won't be retried.

post_webhook_url.description: The URL for post-event webhooks, which are called by using the `webhook_method`. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/webhook-events) for more details.

pre_webhook_retry_count.description: The number of times to retry a call to the `pre_webhook_url` if the request times out (after 5 seconds) or it receives a 429, 503, or 504 HTTP response. Default retry count is 0 times, which means the call won't be retried.

pre_webhook_url.description: The URL for pre-event webhooks, which are called by using the `webhook_method`. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/webhook-events) for more details.

reachability_enabled.description: Whether the [Reachability Indicator](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/reachability-indicator) is enabled for this Service instance. The default is `false`.

read_status_enabled.description: Whether the [Message Consumption Horizon](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/consumption-horizon) feature is enabled. The default is `true`.

sid.description: The unique string that we created to identify the Service resource.

typing_indicator_timeout.description: How long in seconds after a `started typing` event until clients should assume that user is no longer typing, even if no `ended typing` message was received.  The default is 5 seconds.

url.description: The absolute URL of the Service resource.

webhook_filters.description: The list of webhook events that are enabled for this Service instance. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/webhook-events) for more details.

webhook_method.description: The HTTP method to use for calls to the `pre_webhook_url` and `post_webhook_url` webhooks.  Can be: `POST` or `GET` and the default is `POST`. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/webhook-events) for more details.
